<body>
    <h1>ESTA Tekton Self-Managed Migration</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>ESTA Tekton can now be installed individually using a prepared H=
elm chart which is maintained and released by ESTA. The preparation and use=
 of this Helm chart is documented in the README of the <a href=3D"https://c=
ode.sbb.ch/projects/KD_ESTA/repos/esta-tekton-helm/browse" class=3D"externa=
l-link" rel=3D"nofollow">esta-tekton-helm</a> source repository (see sectio=
n "How to use").</p>
<p>If you're already using ESTA Tekton as a managed service (ordered via th=
e CLEW Self Service Portal), here are the steps required to migrate your Te=
kton instance into your own self-managed environment:</p>
<p><style type=3D"text/css">/*<![CDATA[*/
div.rbtoc1713959811572 {padding: 0px;}
div.rbtoc1713959811572 ul {margin-left: 0px;}
div.rbtoc1713959811572 li {margin-left: 0px;padding-left: 0px;}

/*]]>*/</style></p>
<div class=3D"toc-macro rbtoc1713959811572">
<ul class=3D"toc-indentation">
<li><span class=3D"TOCOutline">1</span> <a href=3D"#ESTATektonSelfManagedMi=
gration-BackuptheTektonResultsDatabase">Backup the Tekton Results Database<=
/a></li>
<li><span class=3D"TOCOutline">2</span> <a href=3D"#ESTATektonSelfManagedMi=
gration-(A)MigratetheOpenShiftNamespace">(A) Migrate the OpenShift Namespac=
e</a></li>
<li><span class=3D"TOCOutline">3</span> <a href=3D"#ESTATektonSelfManagedMi=
gration-(B)CreateanewOpenShiftNamespace">(B) Create a new OpenShift Namespa=
ce</a></li>
<li><span class=3D"TOCOutline">4</span> <a href=3D"#ESTATektonSelfManagedMi=
gration-ShutdownthemanagedESTATektoninstance">Shut down the managed ESTA Te=
kton instance</a></li>
<li><span class=3D"TOCOutline">5</span> <a href=3D"#ESTATektonSelfManagedMi=
gration-InstallESTATektonviaArgoCD">Install ESTA Tekton via ArgoCD</a></li>
<li><span class=3D"TOCOutline">6</span> <a href=3D"#ESTATektonSelfManagedMi=
gration-RestoretheTektonResultsDatabase">Restore the Tekton Results Databas=
e</a></li>
</ul>
</div>
<p></p>
<h2 id=3D"ESTATektonSelfManagedMigration-BackuptheTektonResultsDatabase">Ba=
ckup the Tekton Results Database</h2>
<p>For new Tekton instances, a new database schema for storing pipeline run=
s will be created. In order to preserve the build history, we recommend to =
dump the existing database and later import the records into the new schema=
.</p>
<ol>
<li>Get the database credentials from the secret named "tekton-results-post=
gres" in the existing Tekton namespace</li>
<li>Use <a href=3D"https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/app-pgdump.html"=
 class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">pg_dump</a> to copy all data into=
 a local file</li>
</ol>
<p>Here's a shell script that performs these actions:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>backup-tekton-db.sh</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"># 1. lo=
g in to the cluster that hosts your current Tekton namespace
# oc login ....

export TEKTON_NAMESPACE=3D"&lt;your-tekton-namespace&gt;"
export POSTGRES_SCHEMA=3D$(echo "$TEKTON_NAMESPACE" | sed 's/-/_/g')

for key in DB_HOST POSTGRES_DB POSTGRES_USER POSTGRES_PASSWORD; do
  export $key=3D$(oc get secret tekton-results-postgres -n $TEKTON_NAMESPAC=
E -o jsonpath=3D"{.data.$key}" | base64 -d);
done

PGPASSWORD=3D"$POSTGRES_PASSWORD" pg_dump -U $POSTGRES_USER -h $DB_HOST -p =
5432 -n $POSTGRES_SCHEMA --no-privileges --no-comments --data-only $POSTGRE=
S_DB &gt; tekton-results-dump.sql</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"ESTATektonSelfManagedMigration-(A)MigratetheOpenShiftNamespace">(=
A) Migrate the OpenShift Namespace</h2>
<p>For a smooth transition it's best to keep the existing namespace but sim=
ply replace the deployment of ESTA Tekton. The following steps are required=
:</p>
<ol>
<li>Change the label c<code>lew.sbb.ch/project-type: build</code> to the va=
lue "<code>build-self"</code></li>
<li>Add the label <code>iam.sbb.ch/appregistration: "true"</code></li>
<li>Remove sensitive secrets: <em>azure-ad-client-credentials, esta-owasp-d=
b-secret, esta-tekton-smtp-auth, esta-tekton-sonar-api-key</em></li>
<li>Grant admin rights to the new owner/customer</li>
</ol>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">admin-role-binding.yaml</b><span class=3D"collapse-=
source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-contro=
l-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Quelle erweit=
ern</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: yml; gutter: false; theme: Confluence; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Conf=
luence">apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
kind: RoleBinding
metadata:
  name: admin-uXXXXXX
subjects:
  - kind: User
    apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io
    name: uXXXXXX
roleRef:
  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io
  kind: ClusterRole
  name: admin

</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<p class=3D"title conf-macro-render">IMPORTANT</p><span class=3D"aui-icon a=
ui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-information-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>The label <code>clew.sbb.ch/project-type</code> can only be changed by a=
 cluster admin. Reach out to the CON team to get this done.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"ESTATektonSelfManagedMigration-(B)CreateanewOpenShiftNamespace">(=
B) Create a new OpenShift Namespace</h2>
<p>Order a new OpenShift namespace via the <a href=3D"https://self.sbb-clou=
d.net/tools/openshift/standalone" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">=
CLEW Self Service Portal</a>. Tekton namespaces <strong>can only be created=
 on the clusters <em>aws01t</em> and <em>aws02t</em></strong>.</p>
<p>In order to keep the URL to your Tekton instance unchanged, we recommend=
 to choose the same name as the existing namespace (e.g. clew-tekton) but s=
elect another cluster. So if your current namespace is on aws01t, create th=
e new one on aws02t and vice versa. Of course, you can choose any name you =
want but the URL pointing to your Tekton instance will contain the namespac=
e name.</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<p class=3D"title conf-macro-render">IMPORTANT</p><span class=3D"aui-icon a=
ui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-information-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
At the time of writing, some changes to the namespace template need to be a=
pplied manually be the Container Team. Please open a CLEW Support issue wit=
h the component "OpenShift" to get the default limit ranges and resource qu=
otas removed from your Tekton namespace and to get the label <code>clew.sbb=
.ch/project-type: build-self</code> added.
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"ESTATektonSelfManagedMigration-ShutdownthemanagedESTATektoninstan=
ce">Shut down the managed ESTA Tekton instance</h2>
<ol>
<li>Remove the according application from the <a href=3D"https://code.sbb.c=
h/projects/KD_ESTA/repos/esta-apps-argocd/browse" class=3D"external-link" r=
el=3D"nofollow">ESTA ArgoCD Git repository</a>.</li>
<li>Sync ArgoCD (should be done automatically)</li>
</ol>
<h2 id=3D"ESTATektonSelfManagedMigration-InstallESTATektonviaArgoCD">Instal=
l ESTA Tekton via ArgoCD</h2>
<ol>
<li><p class=3D"auto-cursor-target">Follow the "How to use" section in the =
<a href=3D"https://code.sbb.ch/projects/KD_ESTA/repos/esta-tekton-helm/brow=
se/README.md" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">README</a> and creat=
e a new application in your in your ArgoCD Git repository with two values f=
iles providing all the mandatory chart values listed in the README. One con=
taining the public settings for your setup and one containing the secret va=
lues like client secrets, usernames, passwords, etc. The latter one should =
be encrypted with <a href=3D"/display/CLEW/ArgoCD+Setup+and+Configuration#A=
rgoCDSetupandConfiguration-ManageSecretValueswithSOPSandGPG">SOPS</a> befor=
e checking it in to Git.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">applica=
tions/esta-tekton/
  - Chart.yaml
  - values.yaml
  - secrets.yaml</pre>
</div>
</div><p class=3D"auto-cursor-target">See <a href=3D"https://code.sbb.ch/pr=
ojects/KD_ESTA/repos/esta-apps-argocd/browse/applications/esta-tekton-helm"=
 class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">this example</a> for reference.</=
p></li>
<li>Add an application template to your app-of-apps chart for the cluster w=
here Tekton is supposed to be installed (<a href=3D"https://code.sbb.ch/pro=
jects/KD_ESTA/repos/esta-apps-argocd/browse/clusters/aws02t/applications/te=
mplates/esta-tekton/u233658-dev-tekton.yaml" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D=
"nofollow">example</a>)</li>
<li>Permit your ArgoCD instance to manage the new Tekton namespace (see <a =
href=3D"/display/CLEW/ArgoCD+Setup+and+Configuration#ArgoCDSetupandConfigur=
ation-PermitArgoCDtodeploytoothernamespaces">Namespace management</a>)</li>
<li>Sync your app-of-apps chart in ArgoCD and let the deployment start</li>
</ol>
<h2 id=3D"ESTATektonSelfManagedMigration-RestoretheTektonResultsDatabase">R=
estore the Tekton Results Database</h2>
<p>Similar to backing up the database, we use the (new) credentials from th=
e "tekton-results-postgres" secret to connect to the new database and then =
use <a href=3D"https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/app-psql.html" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">pgsql</a> to import the backupped recor=
ds.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;"><b>restore-tekton-results.sh</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence"># 1. lo=
g in to the cluster that hosts your current Tekton namespace
# oc login ....

export OLD_TEKTON_NAMESPACE=3D&lt;your-tekton-namespace&gt;
export NEW_TEKTON_NAMESPACE=3D$OLD_TEKTON_NAMESPACE
export OLD_POSTGRES_SCHEMA=3D$(echo "$OLD_TEKTON_NAMESPACE" | sed 's/-/_/g'=
)
export NEW_NAMESPACE_SNAKE=3D$(echo "$NEW_TEKTON_NAMESPACE" | sed 's/-/_/g'=
)
export NEW_POSTGRES_SCHEMA=3D"${NEW_NAMESPACE_SNAKE}_&lt;cluster&gt;"

# migrate DB dump to be restored into new schema
echo "TRUNCATE TABLE $NEW_POSTGRES_SCHEMA.results CASCADE;" &gt; tekton-res=
ults-dump.sql.new
cat tekton-results-dump.sql | sed "s/$OLD_POSTGRES_SCHEMA./$NEW_POSTGRES_SC=
HEMA./" &gt;&gt; tekton-results-dump.sql.new

for key in DB_HOST POSTGRES_DB POSTGRES_USER POSTGRES_PASSWORD; do
  export $key=3D$(oc get secret tekton-results-postgres -n $NEW_TEKTON_NAME=
SPACE -o jsonpath=3D"{.data.$key}" | base64 -d);
done

PGPASSWORD=3D"$POSTGRES_PASSWORD" psql -U $POSTGRES_USER -h $DB_HOST -p 543=
2 -d $POSTGRES_DB -f tekton-results-dump.sql.new</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p class=3D"auto-cursor-target">Finally, restart the controller to pick-up =
the new records from the database:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">oc roll=
out resart deployment esta-tekton-pipeline-controller -n &lt;your-tekton-na=
mespace&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
